<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/14 (Sat.) Forest bathing is trending. / &quot;Good&quot; and &quot;Bad&quot; are incomplete stories. (Host: Mei)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=445&amp;p=463#p463"><![CDATA[
11/14 (Sat.) Forest bathing is trending. / &quot;Good&quot; and &quot;Bad&quot; are incomplete stories. (Host: Mei)<br /><br />#1<br />Forest bathing is trending.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/TfQFCOxsMOM">https://youtu.be/TfQFCOxsMOM</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.health.harvard.edu/blog/can-forest-therapy-enhance-health-and-well-being-2020052919948">https://www.health.harvard.edu/blog/can ... 0052919948</a><!-- m --><br /><br /> Question:<br />1. Do you believe that being in forest/nature often can cure some human civilized iIIness?<br />2. Do you like being in forest/nature? What do you like the most about being in forest/nature? How often do you spend time in forest/nature?<br />3. Which park/nature attractions have you visited and which one is your favorite?<br />4.Have you had any similar physical and mental experience as described by the narrator when/after you visit a forest?<br />5. Please share a park/forest/nature attraction in Taiwan that you have visited with your table members.<br /><br />#2. &quot;Good&quot; and &quot;Bad&quot; are incomplete stories.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.ted.com/talks/heather_lanier_good_and_bad_are_incomplete_stories_we_tell_ourselves">https://www.ted.com/talks/heather_lanie ... _ourselves</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Question:<br />1. When you run into trouble, what thoughts come to mind right away? On the contrary, what thoughts come to mind when you experience a lucky event?<br />2. If a family member, friend, or coworker runs into trouble and wants to talk to you about it, what would you say to them?<br />3. Is there a phrase or saying that always encourages you when you are faced with a troubling event?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25764">Michelle Hsu</a> — Wed Nov 11, 2020 11:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
